docs.abstract: Joe Biden is looking ahead to South Carolina to resurrect his candidacy. There are signs that it may be a bigger challenge after defeats in Iowa and New Hampshire.
docs.snippet: Joe Biden is looking ahead to South Carolina to resurrect his candidacy. There are signs that it may be a bigger challenge after defeats in Iowa and New Hampshire.
docs.lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — Even before the final results from New Hampshire showed Joseph R. Biden Jr. finishing a distant fifth there, the former vice president had flown to South Carolina on Tuesday night for a gathering of enthusiastic supporters. A gospel choir sang about salvation, a fitting choice for a candidate who is counting on this state’s large black electorate to save his third try for the White House.

headline.main: Biden Needs Black Voters to Lift His Campaign. But He Has Competition.
headline.print_headline: Biden, Banking On Black Vote, Has Company

byline.original: By Stephanie Saul, Astead W. Herndon and Jonathan Martin

docs.abstract: A projected 32 million Latinos will be able to head to the polls in November. The Democratic presidential campaigns are hoping to engage them.

docs.lead_paragraph: ﻿﻿A record 32 million Latinos are projected to be eligible to vote this November, putting them on track to become the largest minority voting bloc. docs.snippet: Mr. Price announced he was stepping down after overseeing the chaotic Iowa caucuses that embarrassed the state and national party.
docs.lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Troy Price, the beleaguered chairman of the Iowa Democratic Party, resigned on Wednesday, a week after overseeing the chaotic Iowa caucuses that embarrassed the state and national party and left Democrats open to accusations of incompetence by President Trump’s re-election campaign.

headline.main: Troy Price, Iowa Democratic Party Leader, Resigns Over Caucus Debacle
headline.print_headline: Iowa Democratic Party Leader Resigns After Chaotic, Error-Filled Caucuses
